title: Ask HN: How influential can physical appearance be in professional environments?
text:
I'm talking about ugly/good-looking, fat/fit, skinny/strong, tall/short... etc.
Do you think physical appearance plays an important role to define hierarchies inside organizations and can decide who has the upper hand in debates?

Ask HN: Do any of you have a completely unrelated second job?
text:
From time to time I become frustrated with the non-tangible nature of the products I work on. Then I start thinking of starting a second, completely unrelated job or business. Something like refurbishing garden furniture, simple gardening, or even working as a janitor has come to my mind.

I read about an entrepreneur who always had the dream of becoming a bus driver. When he had a successful (non bus-driving related) business, he made his driver's licens for buses and started working as a bus driver on weekends.

Do any of you have a completely unrelated side job, that you don't do for monetary reasons? Do you enjoy it? Would you recommend it?
